<h2>
Literature and Texts in the Haida Language
</h2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.haidanation.ca/Pages/Haida_Legends/Haida_Legends.html
">Xaadee Gyaahlaangaay, Haida Legends</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Audio recordings of the Creation, Bear Mother, Killer Whale Man, and other traditional stories in the Haida language.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.haidalanguage.org/raven.html
">A Raven Story</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Text of a Haida fable about Raven, with English translation and notes.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.languagegeek.com/isolate/haidastory.html
">Haida Texts</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Two unglossed Haida stories about the Muddy-Mouth People and Raven's creation of the world.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.sacred-texts.com/nam/nw/hs/index.htm
">Haida Songs</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Collection of sacred songs in the Haida language with English translation.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.cthr-mcdp.com/plaques/Haida.html
">Haida Language Plaque</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Canadian human rights tribute written in the Haida Indian language.
<BR>

<h2>
Haida Proper Names
</h2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
https://web.archive.org/web/20091027141347/http://www.geocities.com/Athens/9479/haida.html
">British Columbia Placenames</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Canadian place names in Haida, <a href="http://www.native-languages.org/kwakiutl.htm">Kwakiutl</a>, and <a href="http://www.native-languages.org/nisgaa-gitxsan.htm">Nass-Giksan</a>.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.cbc.ca/canada/british-columbia/story/2009/12/11/bc-queen-charlottle-islands-renamed-haida-gwaii.html
">Queen Charlotte Islands Renamed Haida Gwaii</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www2.news.gov.bc.ca/news_releases_2009-2013/2009PREM0079-000754.htm
">B.C. and Haida Achieve Reconciliation Protocol</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Articles on the official renaming of the Haida Gwaii archipelago.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.native-languages.org/names.htm
">American Indian Names</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Our new fundraiser offering names for pets in Native American languages (including Haida).
